# C# naming and control-flow style

## Naming

- **Class instance fields, static members, and `const` values**: use **PascalCase** (e.g. `PlayerHealth`, `DefaultSpeed`, `MaxRetries`).
- **Methods**: use **camelCase** (e.g. `movePlayer`, `calculateDamage`).

## Braces on every clause

Use braces for **all** control-flow statements (`if`, `else`, `for`, `foreach`, `while`, `do`, `switch` cases that contain statements, etc.), including when the body is a single line.

```csharp
if (true)
{
    return;
}
```

Do not omit braces for single-line bodies.
